;--------------------------------------------------------------
;
NUMBER 2213
NAME Underground clearing
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Hard packed earthen walls support this large chamber against the weight
of the boulders and other surface debris. This area has been cleared of
most of the dirt and gravel which has sifted down from the crater. The
rubble has been pushed against the walls. The floor is soft brown sand,
which has tracks of some sort in it. This room is lit only by a shaft of
sunlight which shines down through the hole in the roof above your head.
Through the loose stone fragments, you can see passages going off to the
northwest and southeast. The passages are more like tubes that you need
to jump up and pull your way through.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEB
CALL 98
EXIT NW 2214
EXIT SE 2219
ITEM 0 70 VAL2=2212
;
;
NUMBER 2214
NAME Abandoned torch
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A lonely, blackened torch has been thrust into a crack in the stones
here. It was put out long ago but is so firmly wedged that it will
probably never come free. This chamber is small and receives no
illumination from the passages running southeast and southwest. Sand and
dirt are piled against the walls.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEB
CALL 98
EXIT SE 2213
EXIT SW 2216
ITEM 0 373
;
;
NUMBER 2215
NAME Mud pool
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room is cooler than the others in this underground network. The
passage to the southeast rises sharply upwards, which leads you to
suspect that you are at the lowest part of these burrowed caverns. The
northwest corner of this cramped space is covered with a pool of mud
from where the water table seeps upwards. Your feet soon become coated
with damp sand and earth.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEB
CALL 98
EXIT SE 2216
;
;
NUMBER 2216
NAME Shifting stones
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This chamber is slightly larger than the others in this wing. It seems
to be a hub of some kind as there are four of those strange circular
passageways radiating outwards from the room's corners. Unlike the sandy
floors which are common in this area, the floor here is coated with
uneven layers of gravel and stone chips. Every step you take sinks you
into these fragments up to your ankles.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEB
CALL 98
EXIT NW 2215
EXIT NE 2214
EXIT SW 2217
EXIT SE 2218
;
;
NUMBER 2217
NAME Carapace mound
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This space contains hard evidence of the creatures which have been
burrowing out these caves. In the center of the chamber is a ghastly
mound of insectoid carapaces. You can see large and small plates of
exoskeleton. You can also see triangular skulls gazing at you with empty
eye sockets as well as the occasional bug leg. There are small piles of
stones surrounding the mound. Something in the back of your mind tells
you that you think it would be very bad for you if you disturb anything
in here. You can exit the way you came in, through the passage to the
northeast.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEC
CALL 98
EXIT NE 2216
ITEM 0 916
EXTEND 0 of chitin plates
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER From the size of the plates, the insects they came from must be at least four feet tall.
ENDIF
;
;
NUMBER 2218
NAME Bone pile
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This tiny alcove is packed with bones, cloth scraps and a variety of
other odd items. The items are all jumbled together haphazardly and this
place shows none of the order which is common in other parts of these
tunnels. The stench is noxious and the whole chamber smells strongly of
rot. This is obviously the place where the Vith dump their refuse. The
only exit is the passage northwest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEB
CALL 98
EXIT NW 2216
;
;
NUMBER 2219
NAME Claw marks
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is less a chamber and more a bulge in the passageway. The tube-like
passages continue off to the northeast and northwest. The floor here is
sandy, but it is firmly packed. The walls near the passages are filled
with loose stone and earth, but the wall to the south is firm. The
southern wall catches your eye. It seems to be made of a soft stone as
it has been marked repeatedly by what looks to be claws. The markings
make no sense to you.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEA
CALL 88
EXIT NW 2213
EXIT NE 2221
ITEM 0 420
;
;
NUMBER 2220
NAME High holes
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This chamber is unusually shaped. It is circular but not wide. The floor
is only about ten paces across. The room is unusually high however. The
ceiling goes up about twenty feet over your head, although it is
difficult to be precise in the pitch darkness. You can barely see it,
but way up high on the walls are circular holes. The holes look to have
openings about two feet across. It is impossible to see where the holes
go or what is in them. There is a passageway which leads off in a
northwesterly direction.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEB
CALL 98
EXIT NW 2221
;
;
NUMBER 2221
NAME Sandy floor
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room is large and seems to be an intersection. The chamber is oval
shaped, as near as you can tell. There are passages heading off to the
northwest, northeast, southwest and southeast. You can't see where the
passages go, as the darkness robs your vision. The floor in here is
sand, and is much looser than in other parts of these tunnels. You need
to walk carefully to keep from tripping. Loose rock and sand are packed
near the exits.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEC
CALL 98
EXIT SE 2220
EXIT SW 2219
EXIT NE 2222
EXIT NW 2223
;
;
NUMBER 2222
NAME Odd glow
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
As you enter this chamber, you can immediately see something different in
here. There is light. The illumination seems to come from the stone
wall on the eastern side of the room. This wall is made of normal stone
by the looks of it, but it emits waves of light. The glow pulses
erratically and changes hue often. The floor is dark brown sand. There is
a passage off to the southwest which has loose debris around it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
MINEB
CALL 98
EXIT SW 2221
;
;
NUMBER 2223
NAME Eggshells
MONSTER_GROUP 49
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is a medium size room. It is triangular in shape and one of the
points forms and exit passage going southeast. The wall opposite the
passage has some unusual debris around it. You can see the remains of a
dozen or more eggshells. The shells are tan with white spots and are
leathery. Much closer to lizard eggs than bird eggs. You're not sure
what exactly laid these eggs here. You see no young of any kind.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
MINEB
CALL 98
EXIT SE 2221
